widgets_values:
### üé• Motion-Controlled T2V Workflow  
`Use your own video to guide motion in text-to-video generation`

This workflow allows you to upload a **reference video** to guide the motion and timing of your generated output. Perfect for matching character animation to real human movement.

üõ†Ô∏è How it works:

1. üìπ Upload your own **reference video** into the `Upload Video` node  
‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉ‚Üí This could be a clip of yourself acting out a scene or performing a motion

2. üìù Write your **text prompt** as usual  
‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉ‚Üí Focus on character details, background, lighting, and overall style  
‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉ‚Üí You **don‚Äôt need to describe camera motion** ‚Äî it‚Äôs already embedded in the control video

3. üîÅ The model uses the uploaded video to extract motion, while applying your prompt to generate a new cinematic result

üìå This is ideal for:
- Character animation  
- Matching action or gesture timing  
- Custom motion reference for fine-tuned outputs

üß† Tips: 
- Match the framing of your character to the composition you want in the final result

---

### üîÑ Swap DWpose with Other ControlNets  
`Use different ControlNets to change how motion or structure is guided`

You don‚Äôt have to use DWpose ‚Äî you can swap in other ControlNets to get different results:

- üåä Depth  
- üß± Normal Map  
- üñäÔ∏è Lineart  
- üßç OpenPose

üìå For lip sync or better facial detail:  
Use **Normal Crafter** with a **close-up video** for the best results.

Just swap the model in the ControlNet Loader and you're good to go!
